class Stack:
    def __init__(self):
        self._items = []

    def push(self, item):
        self._items.append(item)

    def pop(self):
        if self.is_empty():
            raise IndexError("pop from empty stack")
        return self._items.pop()

    def peek(self):
        if self.is_empty():
            raise IndexError("peek from empty stack")
        return self._items[-1]

    def is_empty(self):
        return not self._items
```
All core operations are `O(1)` amortized when backed by a Python list.
